						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">King: Tribhuvanachakkaravarttigaḷ Kulōttuṅgachōḷa (I) Year 41: 1111 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Built in. This inscription refers to a common land that had remained fallow at Kōṭṭūr in Neṉmali-nāḍu, a sub-division of Rājēndrachōḻa-vaḷanāḍu. Also refers to one thousand <hi rend="italic">kalam</hi> of paddy, but the context in which it appears is not clear. </p>						

